The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically connectivity problems, parameterized by treewidth. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to graph theory and algorithms. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a broad category that covers many topics related to algorithms and data structures, including graph algorithms. "cs.DM" (Discrete Mathematics) is another relevant category, as it covers topics related to combinatorics and graph theory. "cs.CC" (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses the complexity of various problems. "cs.CG" (Computational Geometry) and "cs.GT" (Computer Science and Game Theory) are less likely categories, but they could be relevant if the paper discusses geometric or game-theoretic aspects of graph problems.
